**Don't Comment the Obvious:**

```javascript
// Bad: Comments that explain WHAT
// Increment i by 1
i++;

// Good: Comments that explain WHY
// Skip the first element because it's the header row
for (let i = 1; i < rows.length; i++) {
```

**When to Comment:**
1. Complex business logic: "Users get 3 free tries before rate limiting"
2. Non-obvious decisions: "We use polling instead of websockets because..."
3. Workarounds: "This handles a bug in Safari where..."
4. TODO/FIXME: Mark known issues or planned improvements
